reviews.review: The Rise of SkyWalker was first class action, adventure, suspense, & cinematography thrill ride. I have not been this excited about Star Wars since the Return of the Jehdi. The characters on this installment of Star Wars are my favorite and I absolutely could not wait to see this movie. In closing, may the Force be with you always my friends!

It is what it needed to be to end the series. In that respect, it was a fun and fulfilling film. If you are looking for a story arc that has internal consistency, you will miss the point in bringing two generations of a great cultural icon to this kind of conclusion. For that audience, the movie is outstanding.
Love the movie, but I hope it doesnt end there!
Had its good moments, pretty stupid potholes/decisions that could be overlooked, but the movie undoes all the trilogies, including its own

The movie was great. Some parts made no sence however (The sith dagger), Rey being Palpatine and the ending wasn't good. Ben deserved a better end. Rey and Ben saved each other, but Bens sacrifice without mourning from anyone was terribly sad. He should have at least appeared as a ghost with Leia and Luke... and Anakin.Finn suddenly being force sensitive was possibly what he wanted to confess to Rey... idk, I believe that Ben was saves somehow, but mostly he saves Rey in the end and her living alone in Lukes old house made sence... but I wish Ben have gotten a chance to live too... it would have been a happy ending...
My duaghter and I really enjoyed it. A lot better than I thought it might be.
Kind of predictable and I only feel 80% of closure but very very good movie
The pure chagrin the fans must feel. Even with the best special effects its a complete utter failure.

This was the worst movie of the skywalker saga in my opinion. It seemed like they were trying to completely retcon the last jedi, pack in as much fan-service as they could, and barely tried to work that into a story. As someone who's been a fan of Star Wars my whole life, it felt very hollow and pandering.

If all you want from a Star Wars movie is fan-service moments and you don't care if the pacing is awful and the barebones plot doesn't make sense, then you'll like this movie.
